Description: Fragment of round handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine, accreted; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '190'? plus. Name Kleudikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16615? Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1188)
